Web Recon 

1. DNS Query - Collect dns information such as NS, A, AAA, subdomains and other juicy informations. Also attempt Zone Transfer to collect information.

2. Doman Discovery - To find the root domain of a traget.
2.1 We can use WHOXY (https://www.whoxy.com/)

2.2 We can use amass
2.2.1 To get the number of IP ranges hold by the target - 
      amass intel -org "Target" -v

2.2.2 Enumerate domains and subdomains through asn - 
      amass intel -asn <asn> -o <output.txt> -v

2.2.3 We can get the ASN from this website and use it with amass to find root domains --> https://bgp.he.net/

3. Subdomain and VHOST enumeration - Identify all avaialble subdomains and vhosts.
3.1 subfinder -d <target> -o <output.txt>

3.2 amass enum -d <target> -o <output.txt>

3.3 Filter out the data from amass result - 
    cat amass_sub.txt | grep -Eo "([a-zA-Z0-9.-]+\.)*target\.com" | sort -u

3.4 ffuf Subdomain scanning
    ffuf -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt:FUZZ -u https://FUZZ.target.com/

3.5 gobuster
    gobuster dns -d <target> -w <wordlist> -o <output.txt>

3.6 amass
    amass enum -d <target> -brute -w <wordlist> -o <output.txt> -v

3.7 puredns
    puredns bruteforce <wordlist> <target> --resolvers <public_ip.txt>

3.8 VHOST fuzzing 
    ffuf -w /opt/useful/seclists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt:FUZZ -u <target> -H 'Host: FUZZ.target'
    
3.9 Creating permutations of subdomains
      gotator -sub <subdomain.txt> -perm <wordlist> -depth 1 -numbers 0 > <output.txt>

      altdns -i <subdomain.txt> -o <permutated-sub.txt> -w <wordlist> -r -s <output.txt>

3.10 Filter out live domains/subdomains
    cat <subdomain.txt> | httpx -o <output.txt> -title

4. Finding Origin IP address

5. Fingerprinting technologies and tech stack details.
6. Web Spidering
7. Check robots.txt, sitemap.xml, well-known-uris

8. ffuf 
Web Directory Scanning --> 
i.ffuf -w <wordlist>:FUZZ -u http://SERVER_IP:PORT/FUZZ -recursion -recursion-depth 2 -e .php -v
ii. ffuf -w <wordlist>:FUZZ -u <target/FUZZ> -H "<header>"
iii. ffuf -u <target/FUZZ> -w <wordlist>:FUZZ -fs <status value> -fc 404
 
9. Dirsearch
Content Discovery --> 
i. dirsearch -u <target> --exclude-status=403,401 -w <wordlist> -v
ii. dirsearch -u <target> --exclude-status=403,401 -w <wordlist> -r -v
Fuzzing Authenticated Endpoints --> dirsearch -u <target> -w <wordlist> -H "<token>" --exclude-status=403 -v

10. Passive Enumeration via GAU
echo "<target>" | gau > gau_fuzz.txt

11. Passive Enum via waybackurls
echo <target> | waybackurls > wayback.txt

12. Katana
katana -u <target> -jc -d 4 -o katana.txt

